task.summary: Refactor `PSAtSimFunctions` to accept an executable path and validate it, ensuring better encapsulation and error handling.
Remove obsolete `PSAtSimFunctions` class, add `CPUConfig`, `EnvironmentConfig`, and `PSAtSimWrapper` classes. Update `Program` to utilize new configurations for CPU and environment.

Add MaxFrequency property to EnvironmentConfig class
Introduce a new MaxFrequency property to the EnvironmentConfig class to enhance configuration options. Update the constructor to accept and assign the MaxFrequency parameter.

Add SHA-256 hashing method and update frequency type in CPUConfig class
- Introduce `CalculateSha256` method to compute the SHA-256 hash of the CPU configuration serialized as JSON. - Change the type of `Freq` property from `float` to `int` for precision in configuration representation. - Ensure proper validation for `Freq` in the constructor.

Add SQLite database support for CPU configuration caching
- Include `System.Data.SQLite` package in the project file. - Implement `ResultsDB` class to manage database interactions for CPU config cache. - Create methods to initialize the database and add/retrieve CPU configuration entries. - Introduce `ResultsProvider` class to leverage `ResultsDB` and evaluate CPU configurations, checking cache before performing evaluations.

Implement CPU configuration evaluation and domination checks in simulation
- Refactor CPU configuration initialization to use array syntax for better readability. - Add new domination classes: SMPSODomination, WeightedSumDomination, and LexicographicDomination with their respective implementations of domination logic. - Enhance result evaluation process in Main method to include domination assessments based on different criteria. - Update output formatting for clarity and consistency in displaying results and dominations.
